text: Marinović () is a Serbo-Croatian surname, a patronymic derived from the given name Marin, and matronymic derived from the given name Marina. It may refer to: *Dario Marinović (born 1990), Croatian futsal player *Nikola Marinovic (born 1976), Austrian handball player *Jovan Marinović (1821–1893), Serbian politician and diplomat *Smiljana Marinović (born 1977), Croatian Olympic and national-record holding breaststroke swimmer *Marko Marinović (born 1983), Serbian professional basketball player *Stefan Marinovic, New Zealand footballer *Stefan Marinović (16th century), Venetian printer *Vinko Marinović (born 1971), Bosnian football manager and former Serbian international player ==See also== *Marinovich *Marinković *Marinić *Marinčić Category:Serbian- language surnames Category:Croatian-language surnames
title: Marinović
